A law enforcement officer authorized to make arrests shall issue a citation to a child if the officer has probable cause to believe that the child is violating:
§ 10-113, § 10-114, § 10-115, or § 10-116 of the Criminal Law Article;
§ 10-108 of the Criminal Law Article;
§ 10-132 of the Criminal Law Article; or
§ 26-103 of the Education Article.

A citation issued under this section shall be in a format prescribed by the State Court Administrator after consultation with police administrators and the Motor Vehicle Administrator. Each citation shall be signed by the issuing officer and shall contain:
The name, address, and birth date of the child being charged with the violation;
The name and address of the child's parent or legal guardian;
The statute allegedly violated;
The time, place, and date of the violation;
The driver's license number of the child, if the child possesses a driver's license;
The registration number of the motor vehicle, motorcycle, or other vehicle, if applicable;
The signature of the child; and
The penalties which may be imposed under § 3-8A-19 of this subtitle.

A copy of the citation issued under this section shall be:
Given to the child being charged;
Retained by the officer issuing the citation;
Mailed within 7 days to the child's parent or legal guardian; and
Filed with the intake officer of the court having jurisdiction under this subtitle.
